## FAQ

**How many peer mentor sessions can I book per assignment at ANU?**  
You can schedule up to five 30-minute sessions with your assigned peer mentor over an entire semester. These sessions may focus on a single major assignment or be distributed across multiple tasks. If you require support beyond five sessions, you can request a rematch in Week 8, though availability is not guaranteed.

**What is the cancellation policy for ANU Academic Skills Centre consultations?**  
You must cancel at least 24 hours before your scheduled appointment through the Student Portal. Missing two appointments without timely cancellation results in a 30-day suspension of booking privileges. This policy, updated in January 2026, aims to reduce the 14% no-show rate recorded in 2025.

**When are ANU study skills workshops released for Semester 2 2026?**  
The Semester 2 2026 workshop schedule will be published in the Student Portal on 22 June 2026. Bookings open immediately upon release, and high-demand workshops on literature review writing and EndNote typically fill within 48 to 72 hours.

**Can international students access the ANU writing centre for language support?**  
Yes. The Academic Skills Centre employs several advisers with TESOL qualifications who specialise in working with multilingual writers. While the Centre does not offer English language classes—those are provided by the ANU College of English Language Teaching—it does help international students understand Australian academic genre expectations, such as critical analysis conventions and citation practices.

**Is there a limit on how many times I can use the ANU Academic Skills Centre per year?**  
The primary limit is six individual consultations per semester. Workshop attendance has no cap beyond space availability. Peer mentor matching occurs twice per semester, so you can potentially work with a mentor in both Semester 1 and Semester 2. The "Ask an Adviser" email service has no usage limit.

